laced on the protection order. Alternatively the second approach, as illustrated in the example of the Model Domestic Violence Law below, the authority for arrest without a warrant can be explicitly provided in the legislation. 6.34 6.35 EXAMPLES (1)Whenever a court issues a protection order, the court must make an order- (a) authorising the issue of a warrant for the arrest of the respondent, in the prescribed form; and suspending the execution of such warrant subject to compliance with any prohibition, condition, obligation or order imposed in terms of section 7. (b) The warrant referred to in subsection (l)(a) remains in force unless the protection order is set aside, or it is cancelled after execution. Pre-Issue of Warrant Domestic Violence Act 1998, s 8 (South Africa) 139 Domestic Violence Act 1995 (NZ) s 32. GOOD FAMILY APPROACHES TO A CIVIL FAMILY LAW BILL C E D AW I N T H E C O O K I S L A N D S | 2 0 1 0 119 Discharge or Variation of Orders The \u2018variation\u2019 of an intervention order refers to the court approving an application by one or all of the parties to change the terms of the order. The \u2018revocation\u2019 of", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "24d27e68-e29f-4d53-b7c4-eb9a58db789f": {"__data__": {"id_": "24d27e68-e29f-4d53-b7c4-eb9a58db789f", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/advancing-implementation-cedaw-cook-islands-0", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Advancing the Implementation of CEDAW in the Cook Islands", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/advancing-implementation-cedaw-cook-island